    "question": "What are the differences between var, let, and const in JavaScript?",
    "answer": "<p><code>var</code> is function scoped and can be re-declared. <code>let</code> is block scoped and reassignable. <code>const</code> is block scoped and cannot be reassigned.</p>\n<pre><code>var x = 10; var x = 20;   // OK\nlet y = 10; y = 20;       // OK, but cannot re-declare\nconst z = 10; // z = 20;  // TypeError\n</code></pre>",
