    "id": 3,
    "question": "What is the Temporal Dead Zone (TDZ) in JavaScript?",
    "answer": "<p>The Temporal Dead Zone (TDZ) is the phase where a <code>let</code> or <code>const</code> variable exists in scope but cannot be accessed before its declaration line. Touching it throws a <code>ReferenceError</code>.</p>\n<pre><code>{\n  // console.log(name); // ReferenceError\n  let name = \"Rahul\"; // TDZ ends here\n  console.log(name);  // \"Rahul\"\n}\n</code></pre>",
