    "id": 46,
    "question": "What is a closure in JavaScript?",
    "answer": "<p>A closure is a function that remembers and accesses variables from the scope where it was created, even after that scope has finished running.</p>\n<pre><code>function counter() {\n  let n = 0;\n  return () => ++n;\n}\nconst c = counter(); c(); c(); // 1, 2\n</code></pre>",
